27. Cut 1st and 3rd Columns from /etc/passwd
bashcut -d: -f1,3 /etc/passwd
Sample output:
root:0
daemon:1
bin:2
sys:3
...

28. Count Logged-In Users + Trap Output with tee
bashwho | tee users_logged_in | wc -l
tee simultaneously writes who output to users_logged_in and passes it to wc -l for counting.

29. Convert mystates to Uppercase
bashtr 'a-z' 'A-Z' < mystates
Output:
SIKKIM
MEGHALAYA
MANIPUR
NAGALAND
ARUNACHAL PRADESH

30. Display Common Values Between Two Files
bashprintf "apple\nbanana\ncherry\ndate\nelderberry\n" > file1.txt
printf "banana\ndate\nfig\ngrape\napple\n" > file2.txt

comm -12 <(sort file1.txt) <(sort file2.txt)
Output (common values):
apple
banana
date
comm -12 suppresses lines unique to file1 and file2, showing only common lines. Files must be sorted first.